  • 0.1 Hallmark gene sets

gene sets downloaded from http://bioinf.wehi.edu.au/software/MSigDB/index.html

library(SummarizedExperiment)
library(fgsea)
library(org.Mm.eg.db)
library(pheatmap)

ranking on the statistic (alternative log2FC)

http://bioinf.wehi.edu.au/software/MSigDB/index.html

results <- readRDS("res_HF_v_LF.rds")
results.ord <- na.omit(results[ order(-results[,"stat"]), ])
## Loading required package: DESeq2
ranks <- results.ord$log2FoldChange
names(ranks) <- mapIds(org.Mm.eg.db, keys = rownames(results.ord), keytype = "ENSEMBL",
       column = "ENTREZID", multiVals = "first")
## 'select()' returned 1:many mapping between keys and columns

0.1 Hallmark gene sets

load("share/mouse_H_v5.rdata")
pathways <- Mm.H
fgseaRes <- fgsea(pathways, ranks, minSize=15, maxSize = 500, nperm=1000)
## Warning in fgsea(pathways, ranks, minSize = 15, maxSize = 500, nperm =
## 1000): There are duplicate gene names, fgsea may produce unexpected results
topPathwaysUp <- fgseaRes[ES > 0][head(order(pval), n=10), pathway]
topPathwaysDown <- fgseaRes[ES < 0][head(order(pval), n=10), pathway]
topPathways <- c(topPathwaysUp, rev(topPathwaysDown))
plotGseaTable(pathways[topPathways], ranks, fgseaRes, 
              gseaParam = 0.5)

0.2 curated gene sets

## 1000): There are duplicate gene names, fgsea may produce unexpected results
